Thank you.

921
01:09:04,706 --> 01:09:07,698
Actually,
what I was going to say was...

922
01:09:09,011 --> 01:09:14,074
...if I'd said yes to you
and gone to Madagascar,

923
01:09:14,149 --> 01:09:18,017
then neither of us would be here now.

924
01:09:18,120 --> 01:09:21,886
I just thought that might
count for something.

925
01:09:25,260 --> 01:09:27,160
It doesn't matter.

926
01:09:50,219 --> 01:09:55,816
All right, computer, take us to...
Where are we... Where we headed again?

927
01:09:55,892 --> 01:09:59,350
Okay, I'm gonna get you
another lemon.

928
01:09:59,429 --> 01:10:01,420
All right.

929
01:10:05,001 --> 01:10:08,164
<i>Engaging Improbability Drive. </i>

930
01:10:08,237 --> 01:10:12,139
No, Zaphod, no.
Buttons are not toys. What did you do?

931
01:10:12,208 --> 01:10:14,073
<i>Magrathean coordinates accepted. </i>

932
01:10:21,918 --> 01:10:24,546
<i>It blows my circuits to tell you</i>

933
01:10:24,620 --> 01:10:28,021
<i>that we're in orbit,
at an altitude of 300 miles,</i>

934
01:10:28,124 --> 01:10:31,753
<i>around the legendary planet
of Magrathea. </i>

935
01:10:31,861 --> 01:10:34,557
Magrathea! Magrathea!

936
01:10:35,733 --> 01:10:38,224
Magrathea!

937
01:10:40,037 --> 01:10:42,164
Unbelievable.

938
01:10:45,709 --> 01:10:48,678
Incredible.

939
01:10:48,746 --> 01:10:51,214
It's even worse
than I thought it would be.

940
01:10:52,416 --> 01:10:56,716
<i> Greetings. This is a recorded
announcement as we are all out. </i>

941
01:10:56,820 --> 01:11:00,256
<i>The Commercial Council of Magrathea
thanks you for your visit,</i>

942
01:11:00,357 --> 01:11:03,724
<i>but regrets that the entire planet
is temporarily closed. </i>

943
01:11:03,794 --> 01:11:07,594
<i>If you'd like to leave your name
and a planet where you can be contacted,</i>

944
01:11:07,698 --> 01:11:09,791
<i>kindly do so at the tone. </i>

945
01:11:10,901 --> 01:11:14,837
- How can a planet be closed?
- Zarkin' A, cousin.

946
01:11:14,905 --> 01:11:18,341
Okay, computer, keep going.
Take us down.

947
01:11:18,442 --> 01:11:20,000
<i> I'd be happy to. </i>

948
01:11:21,646 --> 01:11:24,342
<i> It is gratifying
that your enthusiasm</i>

949
01:11:24,415 --> 01:11:26,474
<i>for our planet continues unabated. </i>

950
01:11:26,851 --> 01:11:29,445
<i>As a token of our appreciation,</i>

951
01:11:29,554 --> 01:11:32,580
<i>we hope you will enjoy
the two thermo-nuclear missiles</i>

952
01:11:32,690 --> 01:11:35,955
<i>we've just sent
to converge with your craft. </i>

953
01:11:36,694 --> 01:11:39,094
<i>To ensure on-going quality of service,</i>

954
01:11:39,197 --> 01:11:43,429
<i>your death may be monitored
for training purposes. Thank you. </i>

955
01:11:43,501 --> 01:11:45,469
<i> I'm delighted to tell you</i>

956
01:11:45,570 --> 01:11:48,437
<i>there are two nuclear missiles
heading right for us. </i>

957
01:11:48,506 --> 01:11:51,839
<i>If you don't mind,
I'm going to take evasive action. </i>

958
01:11:56,181 --> 01:11:59,412
<i> Something's jamming
my guidance system. </i>

959
01:11:59,484 --> 01:12:01,452
<i>Impact minus 45 seconds. </i>

960
01:12:05,223 --> 01:12:07,384
Computer, do something!

961
01:12:07,526 --> 01:12:11,792
<i> Sure. Handing over
manual control. Good luck. </i>

962
01:12:22,508 --> 01:12:25,238
I need some help.

963
01:12:25,344 --> 01:12:27,869
I can't do this without my third arm.

964
01:12:30,149 --> 01:12:32,947
Arthur, grab my hand!

965
01:12:43,395 --> 01:12:47,126
- Did we lose 'em?
- No, they're coming right at us.

966
01:12:49,768 --> 01:12:53,499
- Why don't I just press this?
- No, we're not back to normal yet.

967
01:12:53,573 --> 01:12:55,598
- What will happen?
- I don't know.

968
01:12:55,675 --> 01:12:59,668
Don't do it! We're here.
No telling where it'll send us.

969
01:13:03,149 --> 01:13:04,616
- Sod it all.
- No!

970
01:13:08,622 --> 01:13:11,989
Wow. Where are we?

971
01:13:14,461 --> 01:13:19,160
Exactly where we were.

972
01:13:19,299 --> 01:13:20,596
And the missiles?

973
01:13:21,668 --> 01:13:27,197
Apparently, they've turned...
into a bowl of petunias.

974
01:13:27,841 --> 01:13:31,572
And a very surprised-looking whale.

975
01:13:31,678 --> 01:13:38,982
<i> And an improbability factor
of 8,767, 128 to 1 against. </i>

976
01:13:39,887 --> 01:13:42,754
We have norm... normality.

977
01:13:42,857 --> 01:13:45,291
Normality, right.

978
01:13:45,359 --> 01:13:48,294
We can talk about normality
till the cows come home.

979
01:13:49,463 --> 01:13:52,489
- What is normal?
- What's home?

980
01:13:52,633 --> 01:13:54,294
What are cows?

981
01:13:55,469 --> 01:13:58,370
A proper cup of tea
would restore my normality.

982
01:13:58,439 --> 01:14:02,705
<i> It is important to note that
suddenly, and against all probability,</i>

983
01:14:02,777 --> 01:14:05,678
<i>a sperm whale had been
called into existence</i>

984
01:14:05,746 --> 01:14:09,842
<i>several miles above
the surface of an alien planet. </i>

985
01:14:09,917 --> 01:14:12,784
<i>Since this is not a tenable
position for a whale,</i>

986
01:14:12,853 --> 01:14:17,881
<i>this innocent creature had very little
time to come to terms with its identity. </i>

987
01:14:17,959 --> 01:14:20,553
<i>This is what it thought as it fell:</i>

988
01:14:20,628 --> 01:14:23,859
<i>Ah, whoa, what's happening? Who am I?</i>

989
01:14:23,931 --> 01:14:27,560
<i>Why am I here? What's my purpose?
What do I mean by who am I?</i>

990
01:14:27,703 --> 01:14:29,830
<i>Okay, Okay, calm down, get a grip now. </i>

991
01:14:29,938 --> 01:14:33,999
<i>Ooh, this is an interesting sensation. 
A sort of tingling in my... </i>

992
01:14:34,076 --> 01:14:39,139
<i>I better start finding names for things. 
Let's call it a tail. Yeah, tail. </i>

993
01:14:39,247 --> 01:14:43,308
<i>What's this roaring sound whooshing past
what I'm gonna call my head?</i>

994
01:14:43,418 --> 01:14:45,511
<i>Wind. Is that a good name? That'll do. </i>

995
01:14:45,620 --> 01:14:48,885
<i>Yay, this is really exciting. 
I'm dizzy with anticipation. </i>

996
01:14:48,957 --> 01:14:51,551
<i>Or is it the wind?
There's a lot of that now. </i>

997
01:14:51,626 --> 01:14:55,687
<i>And what's this thing coming towards me
very fast? So big and flat and round. </i>

998
01:14:55,797 --> 01:15:00,894
<i>It needs a big wide-sounding name
like ow, ound, round, ground!</i>

999
01:15:01,003 --> 01:15:05,531
<i>That's it, ground. I wonder if it will
be friends with me. Hello, ground. </i>

1000
01:15:07,943 --> 01:15:11,743
<i> The only thing that went through
the mind of the bowl of petunias</i>

1001
01:15:11,814 --> 01:15:15,841
<i>as it fell was, "Oh, no, not again!"</i>

1002
01:15:17,086 --> 01:15:22,718
<i>Many have speculated that if we knew
why the petunias had thought that,</i>

1003
01:15:22,825 --> 01:15:28,195
<i>we should know a lot more about the
nature of the universe than we do now. </i>

1004
01:15:32,535 --> 01:15:34,799
What are those things?

1005
01:15:34,871 --> 01:15:38,238
They're portals
to another dimension.

1006
01:15:38,341 --> 01:15:42,801
Right. I don't suppose this
portal has central heating, does it?

1007
01:15:48,151 --> 01:15:50,642
Ah, this is the one.

1008
01:15:50,787 --> 01:15:55,224
This will all end in tears,
I just know it.

1009
01:15:58,095 --> 01:16:00,256
Right here.

1010
01:16:00,364 --> 01:16:04,562
Hey! Whoa!

1011
01:16:04,668 --> 01:16:07,136
Okay, in we go!

1012
01:16:07,204 --> 01:16:12,369
We can't just step into that... that!
We don't know where it leads.

1013
01:16:12,443 --> 01:16:14,570
If we pick the wrong one,

1014
01:16:14,678 --> 01:16:18,409
we just... we come back,
we pick another one. It's no biggie.

1015
01:16:18,515 --> 01:16:22,110
What? Yeah, it's a big biggie,
Ford. A big biggie.

1016
01:16:22,219 --> 01:16:27,213
What if it rips us all into
tiny little atomic particle thingies?

1017
01:16:27,291 --> 01:16:30,852
This is the right one. I have a hunch.

1018
01:16:30,928 --> 01:16:35,126
- Ford!
- His hunches are good.

1019
01:16:35,232 --> 01:16:37,632
Arthur, I say we go.

1020
01:16:37,734 --> 01:16:43,604
Go with the hunch of a man
whose brain is fuelled by lemons?!

1021
01:16:43,675 --> 01:16:45,336
This is suicide!

1022
01:16:45,410 --> 01:16:49,471
- I think I resent that.
- I don't care.

1023
01:16:49,547 --> 01:16:52,448
I'm getting hostility
from you, Alex...

1024
01:16:52,517 --> 01:16:56,078
- Arthur!
- Have you ever tried yoga?

1025
01:16:57,288 --> 01:17:00,883
- Trillian!
- I think that's supposed to happen.

1026
01:17:05,730 --> 01:17:09,131
She's gone!
Ford, she's gone!

1027
01:17:09,234 --> 01:17:12,226
Arthur, don't panic!

1028
01:17:13,938 --> 01:17:17,874
- Ford!
- Hey, wait for me!

1029
01:17:18,610 --> 01:17:20,942
Whoo!

1030
01:17:31,423 --> 01:17:33,186
Come on.

1031
01:17:33,259 --> 01:17:39,289
Idiot! Come on, come on,
come on, come on!

1032
01:17:43,002 --> 01:17:45,402
Ahhh!

1033
01:18:00,319 --> 01:18:04,016
No, no, no, don't leave.
Come on, come on, just start!

1034
01:18:04,089 --> 01:18:07,217
I told you this would end in tears.

1035
01:18:07,326 --> 01:18:09,419
Did you? Did you?

1036
01:18:17,237 --> 01:18:20,434
Geronimo!

1037
01:18:20,540 --> 01:18:23,031
Ooomph!

1038
01:18:23,143 --> 01:18:27,637
Far out! Far out! Ha-ha!

1039
01:18:27,714 --> 01:18:32,413
This is it. This is it!
Deep Thought. I'm a-coming.

1040
01:18:35,222 --> 01:18:41,559
So, this is how
it's all going to end, is it?

1041
01:18:41,628 --> 01:18:46,565
Me, alone on a dead planet,
with a manically depressed robot.

1042
01:18:46,633 --> 01:18:49,101
You think you've got problems.

1043
01:18:49,202 --> 01:18:51,727
What if you are
a manically depressed robot?

1044
01:18:51,838 --> 01:18:53,032
Excuse me.

1045
01:18:53,106 --> 01:18:57,065
- Aaaaagghhh!
- Whoa, whoa.

1046
01:19:00,113 --> 01:19:04,743
- Who are you?
- No, uh, my name is not important.

1047
01:19:04,852 --> 01:19:08,413
Uh, you must come with me.

1048
01:19:08,489 --> 01:19:12,755
- Get away.
- Terrible events are afoot.

1049
01:19:12,860 --> 01:19:16,387
Um, you... you must come
or you'll be late.

1050
01:19:16,464 --> 01:19:18,728
- Late? What for?
- What?

1051
01:19:18,799 --> 01:19:24,328
No, no. What's...
what's your name, Earthman?

1052
01:19:25,306 --> 01:19:27,706
- Dent. Arthur Dent.
- Well...

1053
01:19:27,775 --> 01:19:30,505
late as in
"the late Dentarthurdent. "

1054
01:19:31,245 --> 01:19:35,147
It's a sort of threat, do you see? No.

1055
01:19:35,249 --> 01:19:38,241
- No.
- Your friends are safe.

1056
01:19:38,319 --> 01:19:41,584
- You can trust me.
- A man who won't tell me his name?

1057
01:19:41,656 --> 01:19:46,423
Okay, my name is, um...

1058
01:19:46,494 --> 01:19:50,430
...my name is... is...
is... Slartibartfast.

1059
01:19:52,567 --> 01:19:55,661
I... I... I said it wasn't important.

1060
01:19:57,339 --> 01:20:01,537
Well... so my friends are safe?

1061
01:20:01,643 --> 01:20:03,110
Let me show you.

1062
01:20:03,178 --> 01:20:09,083
I could calculate your chances
of survival, but you won't like it.

1063
01:20:34,009 --> 01:20:36,807
Did you know we built planets?

1064
01:20:36,913 --> 01:20:40,940
Oh, yes, fascinating trade.

1065
01:20:41,017 --> 01:20:45,716
Doing the, um... doing the coastlines
was always my favorite.

1066
01:20:45,788 --> 01:20:51,454
We used to have endless fun doing the
little fiddly bits around the fjords.

1067
01:20:51,527 --> 01:20:56,521
But then the galactic economy collapsed,
and seeing that custom-built planets

1068
01:20:56,632 --> 01:21:02,161
are a... are a bit of
a luxury commodity...

1069
01:21:02,238 --> 01:21:06,106
Come with me because there's
been a terrible mix-up with your planet.

1070
01:21:06,175 --> 01:21:08,439
Best laid plans of mice, you know.

1071
01:21:08,544 --> 01:21:12,002
- And men.
- What?

1072
01:21:12,081 --> 01:21:14,072
Best laid plans of mice and men.

1073
01:21:14,150 --> 01:21:18,917
Yes, well, I don't think men
have much to do with it. Here.

1074
01:21:58,929 --> 01:22:01,898
Um, I must warn you,

1075
01:22:01,965 --> 01:22:05,457
we're going to pass through,
well, a sort of gateway thing.

1076
01:22:05,569 --> 01:22:07,799
- Huh?
- It may disturb you.

1077
01:22:07,872 --> 01:22:11,672
It scares the willies out of me.

1078
01:22:11,776 --> 01:22:13,767
Aghh! Aghh!

1079
01:22:40,138 --> 01:22:45,974
Ha, ha, ha.
Welcome to our factory floor.

1080
01:23:07,066 --> 01:23:08,863
Okay.

1081
01:23:08,934 --> 01:23:12,392
All right. All right.

1082
01:23:12,471 --> 01:23:15,338
Yeah, this is it.

1083
01:23:18,377 --> 01:23:20,902
This is it.

1084
01:23:21,013 --> 01:23:24,881
O great Deep Thought!

1085
01:23:24,984 --> 01:23:26,679
We have traveled long...

1086
01:23:28,787 --> 01:23:30,550
...and far.

1087
01:23:30,656 --> 01:23:36,151
Have you calculated
the ultimate question of life,

1088
01:23:36,228 --> 01:23:38,628
the universe and everything?

1089
01:23:38,697 --> 01:23:40,460
<i> No. </i>

1090
01:23:40,534 --> 01:23:43,128
<i>- What?
- I've been watching TV.</i>

1091
01:23:43,236 --> 01:23:44,294
Oh.

1092
01:23:44,371 --> 01:23:48,068
<i>I designed
another computer to do that. </i>

1093
01:23:48,141 --> 01:23:50,439
Oh, right, I forgot. Is it here?

1094
01:23:50,544 --> 01:23:53,308
<i>No, it's not here. It's another world. </i>

1095
01:23:53,413 --> 01:23:55,574
It's on another world.

1096
01:23:55,649 --> 01:23:59,141
<i>It is another world, stupid. </i>

1097
01:23:59,219 --> 01:24:01,687
<i>Or it was until the Vogons destroyed it</i>

1098
01:24:01,755 --> 01:24:04,087
<i>to make way
for a hyperspace expressway. </i>

1099
01:24:04,291 --> 01:24:06,555
Well... Okay.

1100
01:24:06,626 --> 01:24:08,719
You sure you don't have the question,

1101
01:24:08,828 --> 01:24:12,355
or a way to, you know,
access it or something?

1102
01:24:12,432 --> 01:24:14,400
'Cause I think I've done
a lot to get here.

1103
01:24:14,501 --> 01:24:18,961
<i>Oh, shh, shh. The show's back on. </i>

1104
01:24:23,310 --> 01:24:27,371
Well, I don't wanna bother you,
so I'm gonna... Good stuff.

1105
01:24:27,481 --> 01:24:31,918
Great. I'm gonna go and find something
else for my entire life to be about.

1106
01:24:31,986 --> 01:24:35,285
Zaphod, Zaphod,
there's the... the gun.

1107
01:24:35,356 --> 01:24:37,654
- Gun?
- That Humma sent you for.

1108
01:24:37,758 --> 01:24:42,218
- You gave him your head.
- Why'd I... Why'd I do that?

1109
01:24:42,296 --> 01:24:43,991
- Okay.
- That's stupid.

1110
01:24:44,098 --> 01:24:49,195
O Deep Thought,
we were told that there is a gun.

1111
01:25:04,018 --> 01:25:06,282
- There you are.
- Hm?

1112
01:25:06,354 --> 01:25:08,049
Look familiar?

1113
01:25:08,122 --> 01:25:11,614
So it wasn't destroyed?

1114
01:25:11,692 --> 01:25:15,992
Actually, it was.
This is a backup. Earth Mark II.

1115
01:25:19,101 --> 01:25:20,898
So you... you made the Earth?

1116
01:25:21,003 --> 01:25:24,632
Not me alone,
but I... I did my part.

1117
01:25:24,740 --> 01:25:28,005
Ever heard of a place,
I think it's called Norway?

1118
01:25:28,110 --> 01:25:31,978
That was one of mine.
I... I got an award for it.

1119
01:25:39,354 --> 01:25:41,584
Oh, hoo!

1120
01:25:41,657 --> 01:25:45,115
All right, Frank?
That's... that's Frank.

1121
01:25:46,061 --> 01:25:50,828
Ah-ha. They...
they've nearly finished the oceans.

1122
01:25:59,007 --> 01:26:00,338
Zaphod.

1123
01:26:00,443 --> 01:26:02,434
Here, it's...

1124
01:26:04,947 --> 01:26:08,007
...it's just like Humma said.

1125
01:26:08,084 --> 01:26:10,678
- Now you can go get your head back.
- Hey, Ford.

1126
01:26:10,787 --> 01:26:13,255
It's been nice knowing you,
you zarking frood.

1127
01:26:13,322 --> 01:26:14,346
No!

1128
01:26:14,424 --> 01:26:16,688
- Whoa!
- This is a bust too.

1129
01:26:16,793 --> 01:26:22,356
H... H... Hey, man. You know,
you must really be frustrated.

1130
01:26:22,465 --> 01:26:25,366
You go through all you have,
you don't get an answer,

1131
01:26:25,468 --> 01:26:28,062
which means no money or fame,
which you deserve...

1132
01:26:28,171 --> 01:26:30,765
<i> The Point-of-View Gun,
conveniently,</i>

1133
01:26:30,873 --> 01:26:33,273
<i>does precisely what its name suggests. </i>

1134
01:26:33,376 --> 01:26:35,901
Fantastic. Fantastic. Fantastic.

1135
01:26:37,013 --> 01:26:39,982
<i> If you point it at
someone and pull the trigger,</i>

1136
01:26:40,116 --> 01:26:42,710
<i>they instantly see things
from your point of view. </i>

1137
01:26:42,819 --> 01:26:44,787
Give me that thing.

1138
01:26:44,887 --> 01:26:46,855
<i>It was designed by Deep Thought,</i>

1139
01:26:46,924 --> 01:26:50,826
<i>but commissioned by a consortium
of intergalactic angry housewives</i>

1140
01:26:50,894 --> 01:26:53,362
<i>who, after arguments
with their husbands,</i>

1141
01:26:53,430 --> 01:26:56,797
<i>were sick of ending
those arguments with the phrase,</i>

1142
01:26:56,900 --> 01:26:58,959
<i>"You just don't get it, do you?"</i>

1143
01:27:00,204 --> 01:27:04,038
Uh, uh, and you're right,
I shouldn't be so upset

1144
01:27:04,108 --> 01:27:06,372
because life goes on, you know,

